---
  Redundant APIs (Can Be Removed/Consolidated)

  1. KYC Link Duplicate ‚ö†Ô∏è Clear Redundancy

  | Endpoint             | Issue              |
  |----------------------|--------------------|
  | GET /api/v1/kyc/     | Same exact handler |
  | GET /api/v1/kyc/link | Same exact handler |

  Evidence: kyc_router.py:106-107 - Both routes point to the exact same function:
  @router.get("", response_model=KycLinkResponse, ...)
  @router.get("/link", response_model=KycLinkResponse, ...)
  async def get_kyc_link(...):
  Recommendation: Remove /link - keep just GET /api/v1/kyc

  ---
  2. OTP Resend Endpoints ‚ö†Ô∏è 100% Duplicate

  | Endpoint                      | Issue                       |
  |-------------------------------|-----------------------------|
  | POST /api/v1/otp/resend       | Just calls send_otp()       |
  | POST /api/v1/otp/email/resend | Just calls send_email_otp() |

  Evidence: otp_router.py:92-94 and otp_router.py:169-171:
  @router.post("/resend")
  async def resend_otp(request: OtpSendRequest):
      return await send_otp(request)  # Literally just forwards

  @router.post("/email/resend")
  async def resend_email_otp(request: EmailOtpSendRequest):
      return await send_email_otp(request)  # Same thing
  Recommendation: Remove both /resend endpoints. Add resend: bool parameter to /send endpoints if needed.

  ---
  3. Wallet Details Overlap ‚ö†Ô∏è Confusing

  | Endpoint                 | Source         |
  |--------------------------|----------------|
  | GET /api/v1/wallets/user | Local database |
  | GET /api/v1/wallets/     | Zynk API       |

  Issue: Both return wallet details but from different sources. Confusing for API consumers.
  Recommendation: Consolidate into single endpoint with ?source=local|zynk parameter, or rename for clarity.

  ---
  Summary of Removable Endpoints

  | Count | Endpoints                                                                                       |
  |-------|-------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------|
  | 4     | /api/v1/kyc/link, /api/v1/otp/resend, /api/v1/otp/email/resend, one of the wallet GET endpoints |

  ---
  Missing APIs (Should Be Added)

  High Priority üî¥

  | Endpoint                          | Purpose                           |
  |-----------------------------------|-----------------------------------|
  | GET /api/v1/user/profile          | Get current user's profile        |
  | PUT /api/v1/user/profile          | Update profile (name, phone, DOB) |
  | POST /api/v1/auth/verify-email    | Email verification after signup   |
  | GET /api/v1/auth/sessions         | List all active login sessions    |
  | DELETE /api/v1/auth/sessions/{id} | Revoke a specific session         |

  Medium Priority üü°

  | Endpoint                                  | Purpose                             |
  |-------------------------------------------|-------------------------------------|
  | DELETE /api/v1/user                       | Account deletion (GDPR compliance)  |
  | POST /api/v1/kyc/retry                    | Resubmit KYC after rejection        |
  | GET /api/v1/wallets/transactions          | Get transactions for default wallet |
  | POST /api/v1/wallets/{id}/transfer        | Initiate fund transfer              |
  | GET /api/v1/wallets/{id}/transfer/prepare | Prepare transfer (for signing)      |

  Nice to Have üü¢

  | Endpoint                            | Purpose                   |
  |-------------------------------------|---------------------------|
  | GET /api/v1/notifications           | User notifications        |
  | PUT /api/v1/notifications/{id}/read | Mark notification as read |
  | POST /api/v1/auth/2fa/enable        | Enable 2FA                |
  | POST /api/v1/auth/2fa/disable       | Disable 2FA               |
  | GET /api/v1/auth/2fa/status         | Check 2FA status          |
  | GET /api/v1/user/activity           | Login/activity history    |

  ---
  Summary

  | Category                  | Count       |
  |---------------------------|-------------|
  | Redundant (remove)        | 4 endpoints |
  | Missing (high priority)   | 5 endpoints |
  | Missing (medium priority) | 5 endpoints |
  | Missing (nice to have)    | 6 endpoints |

  The biggest gaps are user profile management and email verification - these are standard features users expect. The session management APIs would also improve security by letting users see/revoke active logins.

